column5: travis: update to Go 1.9 + remove GOROOT fix
remove test coverage (I don't care anymore)

update travis config

- dist: trusty
- Go 1.8.3 / 1.9beta2
update readme: fix link for gamma explanation
cache/groupcache: fix uniqueness of group name in tests
http: remove unused argument in Handler.setImageHeaderCommon()
source/file: remove parallelism in benchmarks, it fixes a data race, and is not really useful
source/http: add more tested format to TestIdentifyHeader()

source/http: add Server.Identify field.

It allows to identify image format in a custom way.
By default, it uses IdentifyHeader (it uses the "Content-Type" header).
source/http: refactor tests: use test cases instead of functions
create "source" package and move "httpsource" package to "source/http"
remove argument's name if it's not needed
travis: use script instead of gotestcover
re-nable Travis on Go tip, https://github.com/golang/lint/issues/207 is fixed
simplify advanced example & add groupcache example
update readme to use the new demo URL
update readme to use the new demo URL
graphicsmagick: skip tests if not available

update to Go 1.6

- update Travis config
- add support for image.NYCbCrA

Merge pull request #9 from shawnps/patch-1

Add Go Report Card badge
add note about backward compatibility (inspired by https://github.com/camlistore/go4 )
use classic benchmark instead of parallel
image/internal.NewDrawableSize(): add support for Paletted image
inline more function calls in image/internal
http.Handler: don't call ErrorFunc if there is an error with the ResponseWriter
http.SourcePathParser.Parse(): don't set the source if the path is empty (+tweak advanced example)

update advanced example:
- disable groupcache by default
- increase default cache memory size
refactor image package (server, processor & encoder test)
improve HTTP test server in httpsource
use path instead of query param in advanced example
add HTTP log in advanced example
use parallelism option in cache benchmarks
remove SetBytes() in GraphicsMagick benchmarks (it's meaningless)
add error type check in tests
add missing error check on Image.MarshalBInary()
change variable declaration in advanced example
create only 1 HTTP handler in advanced example tests
improve flag system in advanced example
testdata: expose a Get() function, and simplify code
use a struct for NewLimitServer (it's faster)
add StringKeyGenerator (+small fix to cache benchmark)

- add maximum size check
- faster
- less memory allocation
